ActOceans Act
PrecisBOWIE SEAMOUNT MARINE PROTECTED AREA REGULATIONS which designate the Bowie, Hodgkings and Davidson Seamounts located 180 kilometres west of Haida Gwaii (Charlotte Islands) on Canada's Pacific coast as a Marine Protected Area. The conservation objective of this initiative is to conserve and protect the marine ecosystem which is characterized as relative unique and an area of high biologically productivity.
